/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 732.0 Tm (Standardisation Between the Wars) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 718.0 Tm (By the 1930s national bodies on both sides of the Atlantic had fixed the sequence and) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 704.0 Tm (meaning of the three colours. Standardisation was driven less by any new understanding of) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 690.0 Tm (human vision than by the growth of long-distance motoring, which made locally idiosyncratic) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 676.0 Tm (signals intolerable. A driver crossing several jurisdictions in a day needed every signal to) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 662.0 Tm (mean the same thing.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 648.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 634.0 Tm (The three-colour light thus triumphed as a bureaucratic settlement. It was legible to) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 620.0 Tm (courts, uniform across jurisdictions, and compatible with the inherited railway palette. Its) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 606.0 Tm (perceptual virtues, real though they are, followed rather than led its adoption.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 592.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 574.0 Tm (Conclusion) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 560.0 Tm (The traffic light was not invented so much as negotiated. Its colours came from the) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 546.0 Tm (railways, its third phase from the courts, and its uniformity from the demands of interurban) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 532.0 Tm (driving. Treating it as one person's brainchild obscures the far more characteristic story) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 518.0 Tm (of an infrastructure assembled from institutional compromise.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 504.0 Tm () Tj
